# File Naming Standards

Keep files organized and easy to find with consistent naming.

## General Rules

- Use lowercase letters only
- Replace spaces with hyphens (-)
- Use descriptive names that explain the content
- Include dates when relevant

## Examples

```
✅ GOOD
cursor-basics.md
daily-progress-2026-04-07.md
useful-links.md
learning-questions.md

❌ AVOID
Cursor Basics.md
dailyprogress.md
links.md
Questions?.md
```

## Date Format

When including dates, use YYYY-MM-DD format:

```
learning-notes-2026-04-07.md
weekly-review-2026-04-14.md
```

## Folder Organization

```
learning-notes/
  ├── cursor-basics.md
  ├── daily-progress-2026-04-07.md
  └── weekly-reviews/
      ├── week-1-review.md
      └── week-2-review.md

resources/
  ├── useful-links.md
  ├── glossary.md
  └── tutorials/
      ├── markdown-guide.md
      └── cursor-shortcuts.md
```

## File Types

- `.md` for all documentation and notes
- `.txt` for simple lists and quick notes
- `.html` for web pages (when you're ready)

This system makes it easy to find files, keeps everything organized, and works well with search tools.